{1: '1', 2: 'Bieble', 3: 'During an attack, troops must be able to quickly assemble and engage the enemy from various angles and disperse promptly once the operation is concluded...', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Bieble', 3: "It's essential to consider the fact that many people may not support the Task Force in the operation location...", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Bieble', 3: 'In the analysis of the operational environments, commandants must not neglect the significance of networks, information, and...', 4: '1'}
{3: "A hand suddenly emerges, pressing against Bieble's shoulder to prevent him from tumbling down the stairs."}
{1: '1', 2: 'Freeman', 3: "Are you okay? I called your name several times, but it seems like you didn't hear me at all.", 4: '1'}
{3: 'Freeman casts a concerned gaze upon his occasionally whimsical friend.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Bieble', 3: "I'm fine. It's just my ranking in the graduation test. It's not doing so good at the moment, so I've been working on it.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Freeman', 3: "...Wait, you don't seriously think you can ace this test just by working your butt off, do you?", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Freeman', 3: 'Sigh... I kinda had a feeling, but man, you sure are stubborn.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Freeman', 3: "You know, you can't pass this test all on your own. Sometimes, you gotta slow down and wait for the others behind.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Freeman', 3: 'The more challenges you fail, the lower your ranking will drop.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Bieble', 3: 'How did you know I failed my challenge?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Freeman', 3: "Knowing you and your personality, I would've expected you to brag about your success already if you had pulled it off.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Bieble', 3: "Hey, I'm not that bad...", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Freeman', 3: "Anyway, I'll share with you all the tips and tricks I've figured out on my own over the past few days.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Bieble', 3: "Are you sure about that? We're still kind of in a competition.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Freeman', 3: "So you weren't listening to me at all...", 4: '1'}
